<script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "FAQPage",
  "mainEntity": [
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What's the difference between a commercial range and residential cooking equipment?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "BTU output (25,000–35,000 commercial vs 12,000–18,000 residential per burner), heavy-gauge steel construction built for continuous 12–16 hour service vs intermittent home use, oven temps holding 500–550°F continuous, integrated salamander broiler options, and parts catalogs designed for component-level service. A commercial range lasts 15–20+ years with proper service. A residential range pushed into restaurant duty fails inside 18 months."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How often should I service my commercial range?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Annual major service is the baseline: igniter and thermocouple inspection on every burner, oven thermostat calibration against a certified probe, gas valve operation check, salamander broiler verification if equipped. Quarterly visual inspection by kitchen staff catches grease buildup before it becomes an igniter failure. Common service parts ride on the van, so a diagnostic visit during operating hours doesn't have to interrupt service."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "My salamander broiler igniter doesn't work. Can you fix it?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes. The salamander broiler is integrated with the range top and uses a similar igniter and thermocouple system, just mounted overhead. Igniter replacement runs $260–$440. A lot of repair shops in LA won't take salamander work because they're not set up for the overhead mounting and the higher heat-zone tolerances. We do, and we keep the common salamander igniters on the van."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Vulcan vs Garland vs Wolf, which is most common in LA?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Vulcan VR series is the most common range we see in LA, mid-priced, durable, parts readily available. Garland Master Series sits a tier above at the premium end. Wolf Challenger XL is high-end ($15,000+ ranges in steakhouses and hotel kitchens). American Range, made in Cypress CA, shows up often in LA-area kitchens because the manufacturer is local, easier parts logistics and direct factory tech support."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Can you calibrate my oven thermostat?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes. We use certified thermocouples and digital calibration equipment. Drift is typical at year 4–7. If the thermostat is drifted but mechanically sound, recalibration runs $290–$540 and saves the cost of a full replacement. If the thermostat is shot, replacement is in the same range. We test before condemning the part."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "My range gas pressure is inconsistent. What's the issue?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "LA gas pressure varies by neighborhood and feeder line. Pre-2000 LA gas infrastructure occasionally delivers below 7 inches water column, which is below the minimum spec for a heavy-duty commercial range. We always diagnose pressure first with a manometer at the range inlet before condemning a regulator, igniter, or gas valve. About one in five \"weak flame\" calls turns out to be supply pressure rather than the range itself."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Do you service Wolf commercial restaurant equipment?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes. Wolf Restaurant Equipment is the commercial line under the Sub-Zero Group umbrella, separate product family from residential Wolf cooking. Different parts catalogs, different service procedures. Challenger XL CHSC60 and CHSC72 are the ranges we see most often in LA. We have access to the authorized parts network and we know the difference between commercial Wolf and residential Wolf parts. They don't cross-reference."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What's your warranty?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "90 days SDAR labor warranty on every commercial range repair. OEM parts carry the manufacturer's own warranty (typically 90 days to 1 year depending on the component), processed separately through the brand's service network. We document every part number installed and the warranty terms apply directly without us as middleman."
      }
    }
  ]
})} />

<style>
  :root { --red: #C8102E; --black: #0a0a0a; --gray: #f5f5f5; --border: #e2e2e2; --text: #1a1a1a; --muted: #6b6b6b; }
  .section { padding: 64px 24px; }
  .section-gray { background: var(--gray); }
  .section-black { background: var(--black); color: #fff; }
  .container { max-width: 1100px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .section-number { font-size: 0.75rem; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.14em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--red); margin-bottom: 10px; }
  h2.section-title { font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 3vw, 2.1rem); font-weight: 800; margin: 0 0 16px; line-height: 1.2; }
  .section-black h2.section-title { color: #fff; }
  .lead { font-size: 1.05rem; line-height: 1.75; color: var(--text); max-width: 760px; }
  .section-black .lead { color: #ccc; }
  .intro-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 320px; gap: 48px; align-items: start; }
  @media (max-width: 768px) { .intro-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }
  .intro-body p { margin: 0 0 18px; font-size: 1.05rem; line-height: 1.8; color: var(--text); }
  .sticky-cta { position: sticky; top: 24px; background: var(--black); border-radius: 10px; padding: 28px 24px; color: #fff; text-align: center; }
  .sticky-cta .cta-label { font-size: 0.75rem; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.1em; color: #aaa; margin-bottom: 14px; }
  .sticky-cta .cta-phone { font-size: 1.5rem; font-weight: 800; color: #fff; text-decoration: none; display: block; margin-bottom: 12px; }
  .sticky-cta .btn-cta { display: block; background: var(--red); color: #fff; padding: 14px; border-radius: 5px; font-weight: 700; text-decoration: none; font-size: 0.95rem; margin-bottom: 10px; }
  .sticky-cta .cta-sub { font-size: 0.82rem; color: #888; }
  .cta-divider { border: none; border-top: 1px solid #222; margin: 18px 0; }
  .cta-detail { font-size: 0.85rem; color: #aaa; text-align: left; }
  .cta-detail li { margin-bottom: 6px; list-style: none; padding-left: 18px; position: relative; }
  .cta-detail li::before { content: "✓"; position: absolute; left: 0; color: var(--red); font-weight: 700; }
  .failures-list { margin-top: 28px; counter-reset: fail; }
  .failure-row { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 48px 1fr; gap: 16px; padding: 18px 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); }
  .failure-row .num { font-size: 1.4rem; font-weight: 800; color: var(--red); }
  .failure-row h3 { font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 700; margin: 0 0 6px; color: var(--text); }
  .failure-row p { font-size: 0.92rem; color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.65; margin: 0; }
  .config-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(260px, 1fr)); gap: 18px; margin-top: 32px; }
  .config-card { background: #111; border: 1px solid #222; border-radius: 8px; padding: 22px 20px; }
  .config-card h3 { font-size: 0.98rem; font-weight: 700; color: #fff; margin: 0 0 8px; }
  .config-card .price { font-size: 0.82rem; color: #e06020; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 10px; }
  .config-card p { font-size: 0.87rem; color: #888; line-height: 1.65; margin: 0; }
  .stories-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(290px, 1fr)); gap: 22px; margin-top: 36px; }
  .story-card { background: #fff; border: 1px solid var(--border); border-left: 3px solid var(--red); border-radius: 6px; padding: 22px 20px; }
  .story-card .city { font-size: 0.75rem; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; color: var(--red); margin-bottom: 6px; }
  .story-card h3 { font-size: 0.98rem; font-weight: 700; margin: 0 0 10px; color: var(--text); }
  .story-card p { font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.65; margin: 0; }
  .scope-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 24px; margin-top: 32px; }
  @media (max-width: 700px) { .scope-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }
  .scope-card { background: #fff; border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 8px; padding: 24px 22px; }
  .scope-card h3 { font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 700; margin: 0 0 14px; }
  .scope-card.do h3 { color: #0a7c3a; }
  .scope-card.dont h3 { color: #b53028; }
