<!-- INTRO -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="intro-grid">
      <div class="intro-body">
        <p class="section-number">01, About This Service</p>
        <h2 class="section-title">A commercial range defines a restaurant kitchen. When it goes down, service stops.</h2>

        <p>Vulcan VR series, Garland Master Series, Wolf Challenger XL, American Range Performer. These are the industrial workhorses LA restaurants depend on for 12–16 hour service days. Restaurant ranges differ from residential cooking equipment in every way that matters: BTU output (typically 25,000–35,000 per burner vs 12,000–18,000 residential), heavy-gauge steel construction, oven temps holding 500–550°F continuous, salamander broiler above for finishing, multiple-zone cooking surfaces.</p>

        <p>Our techs service the full commercial range lineup across LA, Orange, Ventura, San Bernardino, Riverside. Vulcan VR-24, VR-36, VR-48, VR-60, VR-72 (the most common LA restaurant ranges). Garland Master Series M48, M60, U-Series. Wolf Challenger XL CHSC60, CHSC72. American Range Performer ARTGS-244, ARTGS-360 (Cypress CA local manufacturer, easier parts logistics across the LA basin). Southbend, Imperial, Montague heavy-duty configurations.</p>

        <p>$120 commercial diagnostic, waived with repair. BHGS Licensed #A49573. EPA 608 Universal #1346255700410. CSLB C-20 HVAC scope for adjacent commercial gas and refrigeration work that touches the range install. BBB A+. Phones answered 24/7.</p>

        <p>For burner-only and high-BTU wok range work, see <a href="/commercial/stove-repair/" style="color:var(--red);">commercial stove repair</a>. This page covers full ranges with integrated ovens, Vulcan VR series and equivalents with the standard oven cavity below the burner top.</p>
      </div>

